{"id":542920326,"lang":"cpp","time":"7 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1629728264,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"32 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/542920326/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"38.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    \n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        unordered_set<int> st;\n        stack<TreeNode*> stk;\n        TreeNode* cur = root;\n        while(cur || !stk.empty()) {\n            if (cur) {\n                stk.push(cur);\n                cur = cur -> left;\n            } else {\n                cur = stk.top(); stk.pop();\n                if (st.count(k - cur->val)) return true;\n                st.insert(cur->val);\n                cur = cur->right;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n};\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
